SIMPLE: emergency
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Emergency
<hw>E*mer"gen*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Emergencies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[See
<er>Emergence</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Sudden or unexpected
appearance; an unforeseen occurrence; a sudden occasion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Most our rarities have been found out by casual
<qex>emergency</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Glanvill.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An unforeseen occurrence or combination of
circumstances which calls for immediate action or remedy; pressing
necessity; exigency.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To whom she might her doubts propose,⟦br⟧
On all <qex>emergencies</qex> that rose.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A safe counselor in most difficult <qex>emergencies</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Brougham.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Crisis; conjuncture; exigency; pinch; strait;
necessity.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Emergent</ent>⟦br⟧
